In some aspects, the antibody affinity is determined by measuring the equilibrium dissociation constant of the antibody for the immunogenic composition or the one or more antigen variants of the immunogenic composition.
In some aspects, the immunogenic composition elicits an antibody in B cells, wherein the antibody is measured to have a binding equilibrium dissociation constant to the immunogenic composition, or the one or more antigen variants of the immunogenic composition that is less than 10^-7 M, 10^-8 M, 10^-9 M, 10^-10 M, 10^-11 M, or 10^-12 M.
